SIMPLE: topping
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Topping
<hw>Top"ping</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Rising
above; surpassing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, assuming superiority; proud.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The great and flourishing condition of some of the
<qex>topping</qex> sinners of the world.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Fine; gallant.</def> <mark>[Slang]</mark>
<rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Topping</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Topping
<hw>Top"ping</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of one who
tops; the act of cutting off the top.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>The act of raising one extremity
of a spar higher than the other.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>That which comes from hemp in the
process of hatcheling.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Angling)</fld> <def>The tail of an artificial
fly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>something placed on top of another thing, such as a
sauce or garnish on food; <as>as, a three-scoop banana split with three
different <ex>toppings</ex></as>; an ice-cream cone with chocolate fudge
<ex>topping</ex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Topping lift</b></col> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>, <cd>a large,
strong tackle employed to raise or top the end of a gaff, or of a
boom.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Toppingly</ent>⟦br⟧
